## Description
The&nbsp;**Archive Documents (DA)** task allows to load and archive documents into the Digital Archiving 3 software service using the provided Digital Archiving Store configuration.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias** field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the&nbsp;**Store &gt;&nbsp;Resource** field and select the Digital Archiving Store resource to use.

> Note

For more information,&nbsp;see: [Digital Archiving Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-store-resource-reference).

- In the&nbsp;**Input &gt; Index pattern**, enter the&nbsp;name of the XML index file or a filename pattern (in glob format) to identify it.

> Note

The default value is&nbsp;*LOADER.DA.INDEX.xml*.

> Note

For more information on the structure of the DA3 Loader index file, see [Digital Archiving 3 Loader Index File](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-3-loader-index-file).

## Input
The input of the task is an XML file following the structure of the[ Digital Archiving 3 Loader Index File](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-3-loader-index-file).

If the input contains a pre-filled unique document identifier attribute, for example one created by the [Transform files (DT)](/doxee-platform/docs/transform-content-dt-on-demand-workflow-task-reference) task, this document identifier will be propagated to the output of the task.

If the input doesn't contain a document identifier, the task will fill the unique document identifier attribute with the automatically generated document identifier on the Digital Archiving system.

## Output
The output of the task is the *LOADER.DA.INDEX.xml* file enriched with document metadata and an automatically generated document identifier (if no other GUID has been provided in the input).

> Note

For more information on the structure of the DA3 Loader index file, see [Digital Archiving 3 Loader Index File](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-3-loader-index-file).
